<TITLE> Dramatic arrest at court premises </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 28 (bdnews24.com)  Police were involved in a dramatic arrest of a suspect in the murder of sub-inspector Gautam Roy at the judge's court in Dhaka on Wednesday. Jony Hossain Manik, wanted for the murder, had come to the First Additional Metropolitan Judge's Court in Dhaka to appear in a separate case. Sensing that law enforcers were pursuing him, Jony jumped from the first floor balcony to try and escape. But a driver named Mohammad Manju tripped him up, allowing the detective branch officials to catch him, sub-inspector Shuruj Al Mamun, who was on duty at the premises, told bdnews24.com The police official said that Ahmed Ali Haider, who was earlier arrested in the murder case, had revealed Jony's involvement in the murder in an earlier statement that he had given to the court. Goutom Roy, sub-inspector of Bangshal Police Station, was shot dead in the old Dhaka's Sutrapur area on Apr 20. Three others have been arrested earlier in this connection. bdn
